		<title>04Language Survey</title>
		<content>                                       
Although we live in Wales,there is     
no-one in our class who speaks         
Welsh.For St David's Day we learned    
some Welsh songs and Hymns and Our     
National Anthem.                       
 From our questionnaire we found out   
that lots of people were sad that they 
did not speak or understand Welsh,but  
often used Welsh words every day.      
                                       
              Melanie Watts-7 yrs.     
                                       
In our class we knew;                  
'pop'-lemonade                         
'mochin'-pig                           
'ych-y-fi'-dirty                       
'bosh'-sink                            
'cwtch'-to cuddle or hide something    
'daps'-plimsoles                       
                                       
                                       </content>
